    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Courage on Rights</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Eleanor Levine letter disputes September 23 letter, which favors establishment of trade relations with Cuba and China; notes both countries are notorious for violations of human rights and sentence political prisoners to jail</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A Sept. 23 letter writer argues that we should begin trade relations with Cuba as well as China. But both countries are notorious human rights violators, and both sentence political protesters to jail.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A Sept. 23 letter writer argues that we should begin trade relations with Cuba as well as China. But both countries are notorious human rights violators, and both sentence political protesters to jail.</p>
        <p>Thus, the real point is that if we are going to discuss human rights transgressions, neither country should be trading with us. That, I believe, is the real ''courage'' we should have.</p>
        <p>ELEANOR LEVINE  New York, Sept. 23, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
